    <h2 id="faq">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Is the Keychron Q1 better than the Keychron K8?</summary>
        <p>The Keychron Q1 is better for enthusiasts who want a premium CNC aluminum body, gasket-mounted typing feel, hot-swap switches, and QMK/VIA customization. The Keychron K8 is better for budget buyers and Mac users who want a wireless, tenkeyless keyboard with a simple, reliable experience for around $50 less.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Which Keychron keyboard is better for typing, the K8 or the Q1?</summary>
        <p>The Keychron Q1 delivers a superior typing feel thanks to its gasket-mounted plate, sound-dampening foam, and heavier aluminum case that absorb vibration and produce a deeper, more cushioned sound. The K8 types well for its price but has a firmer, more hollow sound typical of plastic tray-mount boards.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is the Keychron K8 or Q1 better for Mac users?</summary>
        <p>Both work well on Mac, but the Keychron K8 is the more convenient choice for most Mac users because it is wireless with Bluetooth multipoint and includes a Mac-specific keycap layout out of the box. The Q1 is also Mac-compatible and includes Mac keycaps, but its wired-only design suits users who want a permanent desk keyboard.</p>
      </details>
    </div>

